      "isPinned": true,
      "content": "# **\ud83c\udf10 wafer.space Community Rules**\n\nWelcome to the wafer.space Discord server!\n\nThis is a community for discussing open-source silicon, the GF180MCU PDK, and building projects through wafer.space\u2019s low-volume silicon manufacturing service.\n\n----\n\nBy joining, you agree to follow these rules to help keep this space friendly, constructive, and enjoyable for everyone:\n\n## 1. Family-Friendly Environment\n\nKeep all conversations safe for all ages.\nNo adult (X-rated/R-rated) content, explicit language, or otherwise inappropriate material.\n\n## 2. Zero Tolerance for Hate\n\nRacism, sexism, homophobia, transphobia, or any form of discrimination will not be tolerated.\nNazis, extremist ideologies, or related symbols/messages are not welcome here.\n\n## 3. Respectful & Constructive Feedback\n\nKeep discussions supportive and positive.\nDo not insult people or their projects\u2014even if you think something is \u201csilly\u201d or a duplicate of your own work.\n\nThis community is a safe place to learn, explore new ideas, and make mistakes.\n\n## 4. Stay On Topic\n\nUse the correct channels for your posts.\nOff-topic chatter should go in designated spaces.\nSolicitation, self-promotion, and advertisements are only allowed in the appropriate channels.\n\n## 5. Moderation & Bans\n\nModerators reserve the right to take action\u2014including banning members\u2014for any reason, to protect the health of the community.\n\nIf in doubt, ask a moderator before posting.\n\n\u2705 By staying in this server, you agree to these rules.\n\n----\n\nTogether we can keep wafer.space a friendly, collaborative, and inspiring place for everyone interested in open silicon.",
